claim.claim-text:
A solid-state disk (100), comprising:
a control circuit (110, 310);
a firmware switching circuit (120, 320), coupled to the control circuit (110, 310);
a first firmware storage unit (130, 330), coupled to the firmware switching circuit (120, 320), and configured to store a first firmware; and
a second firmware storage unit (140, 340), coupled to the firmware switching circuit (120, 320), and configured to store a second firmware,
wherein the control circuit (110, 310) is configured to read the first firmware storage unit (130, 330) or the second firmware storage unit (140, 340) according to whether the firmware switching circuit (120, 320) is triggered so as to startup according to the first firmware or the second firmware.
